Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, Little Red Rooster, Brown-Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, Tennessee Jed, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Touch Of Gray-> Samson & Delilah, Cumberland Blues, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Jam-> Drums-> Space-> Uncle John's Band-> Morning Dew, E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text:
Very overlooked and wonderful energy Strong energy and crowd reactions throughout. Good volume balance between all instruments except organ before Rooster solo when he gets turned up. 

Grade A performance. Drummers synced and playing with enthusiasm. 

Just a wonderful listen.

This Is The Copy You Want As is usually the case, Charlie Miller's version is the one you want to get. I'd overlooked this show until the anniversary the other day, and boy what a mistake. Nice clean matrix, the energy from the crowd is palpable throughout, the mix nice and clean. Jerry's on fire, hell they all are. And that Touch! WOW!
Excellent Recording I was there 35 years ago today. Another great Spring of 87 show, with lots of Jerry energy. Thank you Charlie Miller!
